df-prod
blocks.content: Define the product of a series with an index set of integers ` A ` . This definition takes most of the aspects of ~ df-sum and adapts them for multiplication instead of addition. However, we insist that in the infinite case, there is a nonzero tail of the sequence. This ensures that the convergence criteria match those of infinite sums. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 4-Dec-2017.)

blocks.content: Bound-variable hypothesis builder for product: if ` x ` is (effectively) not free in ` A ` and ` B ` , it is not free in ` prod_ k e. A B ` . (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 1-Dec-2017.)

thm prodmolem3(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, class c6, class c7, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wceq(cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c0), c1), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), c3)))
  -| wceq(c4, cmpt(s0, cz, cif(c6, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c5))))

  -| wceq(c0, cmpt(s1, cn, csb(s0, cfv(cv(s2), cv(s1)), c6)))
  -| wceq(c2, cmpt(s1, cn, csb(s0, cfv(c7, cv(s1)), c6)))

  -| wi(w0, wf1o(cv(s2), co(nat1, cfz, c1), c5))

  -| diffss(s1, s2)

  -| diffsc(s0, c5)

  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c6)
  -| diffsc(s1, c7)

} = {
  a1ii(wi(w0, wceq(cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c0), c1), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), c3))), wceq(c4, cmpt(s0, cz, cif(c6, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c5)))))
  a1ii(wi(w0, wceq(cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c0), c1), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), c3))), diffsc(s0, c4))
  eqtr3d(cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c0), c1), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), c3), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), c1), w0)
  seqf1o(hs0, s1, hs1, hs2, nat1, cmul, c2, c1, c0, cc, cc, ccom(ccnv(cv(s2)), c7), w0)
  adantl(w0, wa(wcel(cv(hs0), cc), wcel(cv(s1), cc)), wcel(co(cv(hs0), cmul, cv(s1)), cc))
  mulcl(cv(hs0), cv(s1))

blocks.name: iprod
blocks.content: Series product with an upper integer index set (i.e. an infinite product.) (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 5-Dec-2017.)

thm iprod(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wceq(cprod(s0, c0, c1), cfv(cli, cseq(c2, cmul, c3))))
  -| wceq(c0, cfv(cuz, c2))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, cz))
  -| wi(w0, wrex(s1, c0, wex(s2, wa(wne(cv(s2), nat0), wbr(cseq(cv(s1), cmul, c3), cli, cv(s2))))))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wceq(cfv(c3, cv(s0)), c1))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wcel(c1, cc))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c1)
  -| diffsc(s2, c2)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
  -| diffsw(s1, w0)
  -| diffsw(s2, w0)
} = {
  zprod(s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2, c3, c0, w0)
  ssidd(c0, w0)
  eqtr4d(cfv(c3, cv(s0)), cif(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), c1, wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)))
  adantl(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0), wceq(cif(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), c1))
  iftrue(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0))
}

thm iprod(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  ⊢ (w0 → prod(s0 ∈ c0, c1)=(~~> ` seq(c2(×, c3))))
  ⊣ c0 =(ℤ≥ ` c2)
  ⊣ (w0 → c2 ∈ ℤ)
  ⊣ (w0 → ∃(s1 ∈ c0, ∃(s2,(s2 ≠ 0 ∧ seq(s1(×, c3))[~~>]s2))))
  ⊣ ((w0 ∧ s0 ∈ c0)→(c3 ` s0)= c1)
  ⊣ ((w0 ∧ s0 ∈ c0)→ c1 ∈ ℂ)
  ⊣ d(s0, s1)

  ⊣ d(s1, s2)

  ⊣ d(s0, c2)

  ⊣ d(s2, c0)
  ⊣ d(s2, c1)
  ⊣ d(s2, c2)
  ⊣ d(s0, w0)
  ⊣ d(s1, w0)
  ⊣ d(s2, w0)

  zprod(s0, s1, s2, c0, c1, c2, c3, c0, w0)

  iftrue(c1, nat1, s0 ∈ c0)

blocks.name: iprodn0
blocks.content: Nonzero series product with an upper integer index set (i.e. an infinite product.) (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 6-Dec-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm iprodn0(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wceq(cprod(s0, c0, c1), c2))
  -| wceq(c0, cfv(cuz, c3))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c3, cz))
  -| wi(w0, wne(c2, nat0))
  -| wi(w0, wbr(cseq(c3, cmul, c4), cli, c2))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wceq(cfv(c4, cv(s0)), c1))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wcel(c1, cc))
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c3)
  -| diffsc(s0, c4)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
} = {
  zprodn0(s0, c0, c1, c2, c0, c3, c4, w0)
  ssidd(c0, w0)
  eqtr4d(cfv(c4, cv(s0)), cif(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), c1, wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)))
  adantl(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0), wceq(cif(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), c1))
  iftrue(c1, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c0))
}
blocks.pretty:
thm iprodn0(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, wff w0) {
  ⊢ (w0 → prod(s0 ∈ c0, c1)= c2)
  ⊣ c0 =(ℤ≥ ` c3)
  ⊣ (w0 → c3 ∈ ℤ)
  ⊣ (w0 → c2 ≠ 0)
  ⊣ (w0 → seq(c3(×, c4))[~~>]c2)
  ⊣ ((w0 ∧ s0 ∈ c0)→(c4 ` s0)= c1)
  ⊣ ((w0 ∧ s0 ∈ c0)→ c1 ∈ ℂ)
  ⊣ d(s0, c0)
  ⊣ d(s0, c3)
  ⊣ d(s0, c4)
  ⊣ d(s0, w0)
} = {
  zprodn0(s0, c0, c1, c2, c0, c3, c4, w0)
  ssidd(c0, w0)
  eqtr4d((c4 ` s0), if(s0 ∈ c0, c1, 1), c1, (w0 ∧ s0 ∈ c0))
  adantl(w0, s0 ∈ c0, if(s0 ∈ c0, c1, 1)= c1)
  iftrue(c1, nat1, s0 ∈ c0)
}
